# SwiftFormat — default ruleset. Only two project-specific settings:
#  - trailing-commas never: SwiftFormat would otherwise ADD trailing commas, which
#    SwiftLint's default `trailing_comma` rule forbids — keep them in agreement.
#  - no --max-width: don't fight SwiftLint's (relaxed) line_length.
--swift-version 5.10
--trailing-commas never
# SwiftFormat's wrapMultilineStatementBraces puts `{` on its own line for wrapped
# declarations, which conflicts with SwiftLint's default `opening_brace` (same line).
--disable wrapMultilineStatementBraces
--exclude Tuist,Derived,.build,**/Generated
